				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Jun 05, 2005 2:04 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 2084<br /><b>Location:</b> Minneapolis, Minnesota, United States
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you make a fighting game, you'd want to have larger sprites. You'd definitely want to use 8x16 sprites for this reason. I think 6x4 sprites sounds like a reasonable size for metasprites. With 8x16 sprites, you can get taller sprites using less. But you probably don't want to do much sprite layering, as you'd interfere with the limit of 8 sprites per scanline a lot.
<br />
<br />Thankfully for backgrounds and the title screen, you could fit those all into one bank. I'd also suggest having like a 64x30 tile arena (2 screens wide, 1 tall). That would be easy enough.
<br />
<br />The most difficult challenge would be making a decent fighting game with only 2 buttons. I suggest that up would be jump. Would you have lots of combos? I would probably have pre-defined combos, but a lot of them for individual characters. It would be easier to program.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
